content_vision: I'm a loser. Women dislike me. I was caught in a spotlight, when I tried to approach a woman in a bar and failed miserably. Everyone laughs at me. I have sarcasm and witty self-hate still left in me.
text:
Verse 1:
it's a sad story, same old song,
you know the memo, can't sing along,
but tomorrow's a new morning, righting all wrongs.
in this crazy life, there are moments that bring me down,
but i laugh at those, they can't break me, i wear my crown.
ain't no real ones in this game, they all fakes,
taking my air with their rhymes, it's all just poison, snakes,
but i remember when you told me we'd make it someday,

Pre-Chorus 1:
property pistols, we stay strapped with gold
i mean apes, we wild and we bold

Chorus 1:
every time i come around, they wanna know my game
if they ask tell em, i'm just doin' my thang
can't you tell these outfits cost a fortune?
we livin' lavish, ain't no need for caution.

Verse 2:
and who can say, when our time will expire,
but we keep on fighting with our rusty blades, inspired.
joy comes in the morning, that's what they say,
but things are looking good for me, can't you see it this way?
temporarily insane, but we skate through the pain.
eyes fixed on the prize, i ain't giving up,
you come to me like an invisible pup,
please remember me once more, fill up my cup.

Chorus 2:
can anyone really say when love is true,
when two hearts become one, you just know it do
so if they dare ask, just tell them straight
you and me, baby, we can't break.

Chorus 3:
can't ignore the facts, it's obvious,
my crew is everything to me, personal.
yo, you see what i been sayin', my man?
shit's real out here, can't ignore the plan.

Bridge:
i ain't tryna be used no more,
now you can see what i've been talking about, for sure.
life's like a rollercoaster, can't deny,
but even when you fall, you gotta keep on reaching high.

Outro:
ya, gotta keep it real,
i mean apes, they can't handle our appeal.

Instrumental:
we should be falling in love, not tiptoeing and prancing,
but here we are, doing this little dance, hmphm.
